oai_dc:dc.dc:title: THE WAVE CLIMATE OF SOUTH-EAST AUSTRALIA AND FUTURE WAVE PROJECTION BY THE END OF 21ST CENTURY
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Liu, Jin
Young, Ian
Meucci, Alberto
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: In this study, high-resolution unstructured ocean wave datasets based on a third-generation wave model (WAVEWATCH III, WW3) were developed for south-east Australia. Through this study, we aim to understand the wave climate based on hindcast model datasets and develop future wave projections by the end of the 21st century.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 37 (2022): Proceedings of 37th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Sydney, Australia, 2022; waves.1
